    "description": "This dairy-free pumpkin ginger soup is the perfect warming dish to welcome in fall! The slight bite from the jalapeño and Sriracha perfectly balances out the sweetness from the pumpkin. Whip it up this weekend for a cozy day in!",
    "slug": "pumpkin-ginger-soup",
    "thumbnail_url": "https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/243358.jpg",
    "cook_time_minutes": 35,
    "country": "US",
    "num_servings": 4,
    "servings_noun_plural": "servings",
    "servings_noun_singular": "serving",
    "prep_time_minutes": 10,
    "total_time_minutes": 45,
    "sections": [
      {
        "name": "Soup",
        "components": [
          {
            "raw_text": "1 tablespoon coconut oil"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "1 medium white onion, diced (about 2 cups)"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "2 teaspoons kosher salt, divided, plus more to taste"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "4 cloves garlic, minced"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "1 3-inch piece of fresh ginger, peeled and grated"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "1 medium jalapeño, seeded and minced"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "2–3 teaspoons Sriracha"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "2 14-ounce cans of unsweetened pumpkin purée"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "2½ cups vegetable stock"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "1 13.5-ounce can of full-fat coconut milk, room temperature"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "Juice of 1 lime"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "⅓ cup toasted pepitas"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "Cilantro Coconut Cream",
        "components": [
          {
            "raw_text": "1 13.5-ounce can of full-fat coconut cream, chilled"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "Zest of 1 lime"
          },
          {
            "raw_text": "1 cup fresh cilantro leaves, packed, plus more for garnish"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "instructions": [
      {
        "display_text": "In a large pot, melt the coconut oil over medium heat. Add the onion and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10–15 minutes, until the onions are translucent and softened."
      },
      {
        "display_text": "Add the garlic, ginger, and jalapeño. Sauté for 3–5 minutes, until fragrant and softened."
      },
      {
        "display_text": "Add the Sriracha, pumpkin purée, and vegetable stock and stir to combine. Cover the pot, reduce the heat to low, and simmer the soup for 15–20 minutes, until all of the vegetables are completely broken down."
      },
      {
        "display_text": "While the soup simmers, make the cilantro coconut cream: Add the chilled coconut cream to a liquid measuring cup or tall, narrow container, along with the lime zest and cilantro. Using an immersion blender, blend until the cilantro is completely broken down and the coconut cream turns pale green in color.  Chill the cilantro cream in the refrigerator until ready to serve."
      },
      {
        "display_text": "Remove the soup from heat and stir in the coconut milk. Using an immersion blender, blend the soup until completely smooth. Season with the remaining teaspoon of salt. Stir in the lime juice. Season to taste with more salt, if needed."
      },
      {
        "display_text": "Ladle the soup into bowls and top each serving with 1 tablespoon of cilantro cream and toasted pepitas."
      },
      {
        "display_text": "Enjoy!"
      }
    ],
